HEADWORD: Indocility
<hw>In`do*cil"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>indocilitas</ets>: cf. F. <ets>indocilit⟦eacute⟧</ets>.]</ety>
<def>The quality or state of being indocile; dullness of intellect;
unteachableness; intractableness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The stiffness and <qex>indocility</qex> of the Pharisees.</q>
<rj><qau>W. Montagu.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Indoctrinate</ent>⟦br⟧
